- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed algorithmic architecture can be seen as an application of artificial intelligence in architecture. The paper also discusses the possibility of using computational methods to generate similar buildings.
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality): The paper proposes a computational approach to generate similar buildings, which can be applied in augmented reality to visualize the hypothetical buildings.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the application of computational methods in architecture and proposes a hypothetical algorithmic architecture. This topic is closely related to computational engineering.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper uses the cube counting method to calculate the fractal dimension of the Borobudur Temple, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and pattern recognition.
